# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unrealeased]
### Added
- Support for the Jalali Calendar
- Support for the Julian Calendar


### Changed

### Fixed
- The problem of right to left and left to right things. 

### Removed

## [0.0.4] - 2021-08-24 'Chinese and Rumi-removal'
### Added
- Support for the Chinese Calendar
- Separate file for my personal texts, so each book-progress-update does not warrant a commit
- Support for the chinese zodiac system by adding a function from Codewars that was more refined than the one I came up with
- Some mention of dependendcies

### Changed
- The input of the get_dates function is no longer a string, but of type datetime
- Minor adjustments to the README to better suit the current predicament

### Removed
- Removed the Rumi Calendar from the objectives of this program.

## [0.0.3] - 2021-08-23 'Judea dhe Jacobin dhe Hijri'
### Added
- Support for the Judean Calendar
- Support for the Jacobin Calendar
- Support for today/tomorrow functionality

### Changed
- Changed the date_obj to a dictionary
- Changed the French Revolutionary Calendar to the Jacobin Calendar
- Extracted the date_obj variables and calculations into their separate function
- Changed Hijri Calendar to Qamari Hijri â€“ I would rather shamshi hijri than jalali

### Fixed
- Refined documentation in places
- To some degree, the right-left and left-right dilema

### Removed
- The dvdr as it was not very pleasing to the eye

## [0.0.2] - 2021-08-22 'Dates and cleaning'
### Added
- Support for the Gregorian Calendar
- Support for the ISO Calendar
- Support for the Hijri Calendar
- Voice activities
- Proper documenation of various functions

### Removed
- Sporadic and uncalled for comments
- Unnecessary Functions

### Changed
- Title formations

## [0.0.1] - 2021-08-22 'Start-up'
